<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>PS00068</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : HUMAN RIGHTS OF FARMERS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : 44th Anniversary Of The Declaration Of Martial Law</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : ... Rep. Casilao spoke on the issue of human rights violations particularly on the political and extrajudicial killings of farmers, farmworkers, lumads and indigenous peoples (IPs). He stated that such killings are reminiscent of the martial law era and that the farmers and farmworkers still continue to 
experience such kind of abuse to date...; expressed support on the ongoing formal peace talks between the National Democratic Front of 
the Philippines (NDFP) and the government,...; urged his colleagues to join the clamor for 
the release of some 500 political prisoners and to support House Resolution No.198 filed by the Makabayan Coalition seeking the release of political prisoners...; emphasized the right of farmers to labor on their land in peace, without threat and intimidation, and called for justice for the continuing atrocities of the military against the marginalized sector.(SOURCE: House Journal No. 22,p.11)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>CASILAO, ARIEL &quot;KA AYIK&quot; B.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-09-14</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Speech-Privilege Hour</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE AND FOOD ON 2016-09-21</td></tr></table>